commit_list.message:
Finishing touches (#65)

* Main finished
- Added description 

* Removed old test file

* CLI finished
- It was unclear that the user is expected to write their own review.
- Changed commands and description to clarify this.
- Change the help commands
- Finished commands
- Finished comments

- Updated ability to remove files, all files created can be removed.
- Update candidates info
- Add ability to run all the tests from 1 command
- Added explanation to how we handle stopwords.

* Classifier finished
- Changed variable names, removed some returns that aren't used.
- Renamed variable names
- Updated documentation
- Classifier is only loaded once when classifying user input
- Changes to train
- It doesn't hurt performance much to load the classifier, it only takes around 0.5 sec from the prepared file.

- Text is no longer counted multiple times
- Fix bug that caused incorrect dataset to be used for testing
- Added some additional comments to clarify confusing parts of the code
- Remove unused variable

* data_handler finished

- Updated the documentation
- Added try-except block in remove_characters - just in case
- Removed old function that is not used
- Updated the name of some functions
- Fixed issues with removal of characters in text, New words are no longer created, example: "Hello!" Will now be "hello" and not "hello!"


* Testing finished
- Renamed functions to test_classify_
- Updated documentation
- Added missing documentation
- Add 4 new tests
- Training data can be used to classify testing data and training data, with and without stopwords

* Optimized imports

* Code inspection
- Removed unused variables
- Simplified several some code
- Renamed some variables
- Fixed some documentation
- Removed redundant or useless code

* Preprocessed data is now included in github repo

Write a new classifier and refactor the entire assignment (#57)

* Counting of words is working properly

* training and testing data is stored in ram

- Summerizing all values in huge dictionaries takes a while if you do it all the time.

* Solved the log issue

* Moved functions in to data_handler

* Accuracy is measured when predicting the test reviews

* Refactored testing and cli
- Removed a lot of old tests

* Using count_text everywhere now instead of the one I made.
- make_word_frequency_dict() removed

* Saving the trained classifier to the drive and attempt to load that file when using the classifier

* All files created by the program can be deleted

* Stopwords have returned and increases accuracy by 1% yeee

* Added the ability to see the most common words

* More refactoring

* Added ability to see most common words in training data

* Improved cli experience
- Removed old commands

* predictor is now known as classifier

* The predictions are timed

* Changed the name of the saved test data

* Added some feedback to invalid input
